{"title":"Wilde Moto Cruiser: 3 Bar Homage for $900","link":"https://theradavist.com/wilde-moto-cruiser","date":1772639518000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/wilde-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Wilde</a> just announced an all-new model, the <a href=\"https://alnk.to/2QA5uRW\" target=\"_blank\">Moto Cruiser</a>, this morning…</em><span></span></p>\n<p>The Moto Cruiser is a classic three-bar cruiser silhouette, inspired by Cook Brothers (which are now <a href=\"https://www.ebay.com/itm/257370759473?mkcid=16&amp;mkevt=1&amp;mkrid=711-127632-2357-0&amp;ssspo=BEbBSQ_tT3S&amp;sssrc=4429486&amp;ssuid=aVeCoaanTO2&amp;stype=1&amp;var=&amp;widget_ver=artemis&amp;media=COPY\" target=\"_blank\">fetching $12k at auction</a>), <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/1979-lawwill-knight-pro-cruiser\" target=\"_blank\">Pro Cruiser</a>, Laguna, Littlejohn, Sweetheart Cycles (Later became Yeti), and others from the 1980s. These 26″ wheeled big BMX bikes came along around the time of the genesis of the mountain bike.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-Geo.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-Geo.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Unlike classic cruisers, Wilde’s Moto Cruiser comes in four sizes. It was designed to be as easy to build up as possible from your parts bin or local used bike co-op. It takes rim brakes, 26” quick-release or bolt-on wheels, and can be built geared or single speed.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-4.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The looptail, big tire clearance, classic silhouette, derailleur capable horizontal dropouts, and the ability to choose from decades of available used parts, updated with stealth dropper routing and a more progressive geo for maximum playfulness.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-12.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-12.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-12.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-12.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The Moto Cruiser can be purchased as a frameset bundle – frame, fork, handlebar – for $900 or a Deore single speed complete for $1800. Both options are available for pre-book immediately with delivery in June, 2026…</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-8.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-8.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-8.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-8.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Frame Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Made in Taiwan</li>\n<li>Classic “3-bar” silhouette</li>\n<li>Looptail design</li>\n<li>Canti studs</li>\n<li>Bottle mount on down tube (Small &amp; Med) and bottle mount on seat tube (L &amp; XL)</li>\n<li>Three pack mounts under down tube</li>\n<li>Stealth dropper post routing</li>\n<li>Modular cable guides</li>\n<li>Clearance for up to 26 x 2.5″ tires</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-13.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-13.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Fork Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>420 axle to crown (suspension corrected for 80mm fork)</li>\n<li>Mid-blade rack mount</li>\n<li>Tire clearance 26 x 2.5″</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-11.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/03/Wilde-Moto-Cruiser-11.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Handlebar Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>90 mm Rise</li>\n<li>15° Back Sweep</li>\n<li>7 ° Up Sweep</li>\n<li>830 mm Wide</li>\n<li>22 mm Clamp</li>\n<li>100% Butted 4130 Chromoly steel</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Roll on over to <a href=\"https://alnk.to/2QA5uRW\" target=\"_blank\">Wilde</a> to check out more.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/wilde-moto-cruiser\">Wilde Moto Cruiser: 3 Bar Homage for $900</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://cms.theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"a21a76350bee9c4d74ee4aa1454da5d33e76677980eec40f19c4166f79ac01e8","category":"Cycling"}